The paper deals with object detection using a convolutional neural network (CNN) and a search framework, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a probabilistic model, which involves probabilistic reasoning and statistical learning, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a search framework also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
